Columns.Description: The status of the event. Typical values include Started, In Progress, Succeeded, Failed, Active, and Resolved.
Columns.Name: ResultType

Columns.Description: A GUID used to group together a set of related events.
Columns.Name: CorrelationId

Columns.Description: The identity of the user or application that performed the operation.
Columns.Name: Identity

Columns.Description: The severity level of the event. Must be one of Informational, Warning, Error, or Critical.
Columns.Name: Level

Columns.Description: The name of the operation associated with the log entry.
Columns.Name: OperationName

Columns.Description: The AAD tenant ID the operation was submitted for.
Columns.Name: AadTenantId

Columns.Description: The name of the AML service.
Columns.Name: AmlServiceName

Columns.Description: A unique identifier for the resource that the record is associated with
Columns.Name: _ResourceId

Columns.Description: A unique identifier for the subscription that the record is associated with
Columns.Name: _SubscriptionId
